  "texts": [
    "Specifically, when the model was tasked to role-play as an older adult with heart failure, it inappropriately adopted the voice of a clinician, replete with expert knowledge such as WHO guidelines.",
    "This instance highlights a deeper issue of 'source blindness', where the LLM fails to differentiate and adapt its knowledge base according to the specific role or perspective it is meant to represent.",
    "Consequently, this leads to an inaccurate portrayal, as seen in the model's tendency to echo the dominant, well-documented perspectives-in this case, clinical expertise-rather than the authentic lived experiences of the group it is tasked to represent.",
    "This may reflect the LLM being disproportionately influenced during pretraining by whichever voice is more prevalent and vocal online, suggesting that LLMs can propagate stereotyping and bias, a concern extensively discussed by Luccioni et al.",
    "[72] and Glickman and Sharot [73]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "[72] and Glickman and Sharot [73]."
  ]
}